CAPE TOWN - Petter Solberg is one of the world legends of off-road racing.The Norwegian is a former WRC and Rallycross World Champion.He was in South Africa recently at the launch of the Cape Town leg of the FIA World Rallycross Championship.Solberg, a household name in the motorsport fraternity, inherited his love for fast cars from his parents who were keen competitors in his native Norway.In South Africa the legal age to obtain a driver s licence is 18.Solberg was behind the wheel much earlier than that.*Watch video above for full storyeNCA